 :tx/rationale "C9-AGENT-IDENTITY-RESOLUTION: The answer to 'how do you enforce session start?' is: you dont enforce ceremonies, you make them implicit. The session auto-detect already exists in main.rs:136-158 — it fires on the first command when no active session exists. The fix: when session auto-detect fires, derive the session agent ID from something unique to the current process (PID + timestamp). Then all subsequent commands in that process inherit the session agent ID. This composes all three approaches: (1) Explicit --agent flag overrides everything. (2) BRAID_AGENT env var overrides the auto-derived ID. (3) Auto-derived session ID is the fallback — unique per process, requires zero ceremony. The session entity already has :session/agent (Ref). The observe command already checks find_active_session(). The wiring: observe reads the active session agent ID instead of using the hardcoded braid:user default. No new ceremony. No env vars required. No provider-specific logic. Just: first command auto-creates session with unique agent ID, subsequent commands inherit it."
